After their debut in RoboSub 2025, Cyclone RoboSub has spent the past year iterating on our vehicle (Manny the Manatee) to expand autonomous capabilities and ensure reliability for both RoboSub 2026 and environmental research deployments. While our competition strategy has remained similar to that of 2025, we've placed a renewed emphasis on rigorous testing and software reliability. By conducting weekly pool tests, we have been able to rapidly identify both software and electrical issues that typically never surfaced while in the workshop, ultimately helping us to proactively mitigate edge cases. This year, Manny features a new, external stereo vision setup and PCBs for battery telemetry and thruster control along with a rewritten software stack and Simulink controller. By exercising methodical decision making and rapid testing, we aim to optimize our reliability and, in turn, maximize our points at RoboSub 2026.

